  <reg:acttitle>Evidence Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Affirmation Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[includes amendments up to B.C. Reg. 314/91]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e27" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Prescribed form</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The prescribed form of solemn affirmation for the purposes of section 20 of the
          <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96124_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Evidence Act</in:doc></bcl:link> is as follows:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d1e45">
        <bcl:text>"I solemnly promise, affirm and declare that the evidence given by me to the court
          [or as the case may be] shall be the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the
          truth."</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e45">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Alternate form</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Where the form prescribed in section 1 is not used, the prescribed form of solemn
        affirmation is the use of "I solemnly promise", "I solemnly affirm", "I solemnly declare" or
        words to like effect in place of "I swear", "I make oath" or words to like effect in an
        oath.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 314/91.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96124_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Evidence
        Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 124, relevant to the enactment of this
      regulation: sectionÂ 20]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
